Cfigcaption%3EScoop%20out%20the%20core%20and%20flesh%20of%20each%20tomato.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20want%20to%20scoop%20out%20the%20core%20and%20flesh%20of%20the%20tomato%2C%20leaving%20enough%20space%20to%20add%20the%20yemista%20filling%20later%20(as%20seen%20above).%20My%20dad%20recommends%20using%20an%20ice%20cream%20scooper%20to%20get%20the%20filling%20out%20since%20it's%20sharper%2C%20but%20a%20spoon%20will%20also%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20making%20eight%20stuffed%20tomatoes%2C%20save%20the%20flesh%20of%20five%20of%20them%20in%20a%20bowl%20%E2%80%94%20you'll%20need%20them%20for%20the%20filling.%20My%20dad%20recommends%20using%20the%20leftover%20flesh%20to%20make%20a%20simple%20tomato%20sauce%20for%20a%20pasta%20dish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPro%20tip%3A%20If%20you're%20doing%20stuffed%20bell%20peppers%20as%20well%2C%20you'll%20scoop%20them%20out%20the%20same%20way%20%E2%80%94%20just%20make%20sure%20to%20throw%20the%20seeds%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThere%20are%20two%20methods%20you%20can%20use%20to%20make%20the%20tomato%20%26quot%3Bsauce%26quot%3B%20that%20goes%20into%20the%20yemista%20filling.%20The%20easier%20one%20involves%20a%20food%20processor.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tomato%20chunks%20in%20the%20food%20processor%20for%20yemista%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d81e5a0e5a0018d2ed24%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20food%20processor%20helps%20finely%20chop%20the%20tomato%20flesh%20needed%20for%20the%20filling.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20a%20knife%2C%20remove%20the%20hard%20core%20from%20each%20small%20ball%20of%20tomato%20filling%20you've%20scooped%20out.%20Put%20the%20remaining%20flesh%20in%20a%20food%20processor%20to%20finely%20chop%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIf%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20food%20processor%2C%20you%20can%20achieve%20similar%20results%20with%20a%20grater.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Grating%20tomato%20for%20yemista%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d8025a0e5a0018d2ece4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYou%20can%20also%20use%20a%20grater%20to%20remove%20the%20flesh%20from%20the%20tomato's%20core%20for%20the%20filling.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECarefully%20slide%20your%20ball%20of%20tomato%20filling%20up%20and%20down%20the%20grater%20over%20a%20bowl%2C%20removing%20the%20flesh%20from%20the%20core.%20Don't%20try%20to%20grate%20the%20hard%20core%20%E2%80%94%20we%20just%20need%20the%20soft%20part%20of%20each%20tomato.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20be%20a%20little%20trickier%2C%20especially%20for%20an%20inexperienced%20chef%2C%20so%20watch%20out%20for%20your%20fingers!%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EYour%20finished%20tomato%20%26quot%3Bsauce%26quot%3B%20should%20look%20like%20this.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tomato%20mixture%20for%20yemista%20sauce%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d8025a0e5a0018d2ece7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20tomato%20%26quot%3Bsauce%26quot%3B%20we%20use%20for%20the%20yemista%20filling.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELeave%20it%20to%20the%20side%20until%20it's%20time%20to%20make%20the%20filling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EArrange%20your%20tomato%20%26quot%3Bcups%26quot%3B%20in%20a%209-inch%20by%2012-inch%20baking%20dish.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pouring%20out%20water%20in%20tomatoes%20for%20yemista%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d8035a0e5a0018d2eceb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPour%20any%20extra%20water%20in%20the%20tomato%20cups%20right%20into%20the%20pan.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDump%20any%20extra%20water%20from%20the%20tomato%20cups%20right%20into%20the%20baking%20dish.%20(Don't%20worry%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20add%20even%20more%20water%20in%20a%20bit.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELightly%20salt%20the%20interior%20of%20each%20tomato%20for%20extra%20taste.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Salting%20tomatoes%20for%20yemista%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d8225a0e5a0018d2ed31%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDon't%20forget%20to%20salt%20the%20tomato%20cups%20for%20more%20flavor.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20yemista%20is%20almost%20ready%20for%20the%20oven.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ENow%20it's%20time%20to%20make%20the%20filling.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Oil%20in%20pan%20for%20yemista%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d8285a0e5a0018d2ed4d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDrizzle%20some%20olive%20oil%20into%20a%20pan%20and%20place%20it%20over%20medium%20heat.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20add%20a%20drizzle%20of%20olive%20oil%20to%20a%20large%20saut%C3%A9%20pan%20over%20medium%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELet%20the%20olive%20oil%20heat%20up%2C%20then%20add%20the%20chopped%20onion.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Onions%20in%20pan%20for%20yemista%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d8245a0e5a0018d2ed41%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELet%20the%20onion%20cook%20until%20browned.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20onion%20should%20cook%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20minutes%2C%20until%20browned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ENow%2C%20throw%20in%20the%20ground%20beef%20%E2%80%A6%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Salting%20ground%20beef%20in%20pan%20for%20yemista%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d8245a0e5a0018d2ed43%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESeason%20the%20beef%20with%20salt%20and%20pepper.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESeason%20the%20beef%20with%20salt%20and%20freshly%20ground%20black%20pepper%20for%20extra%20flavor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%E2%80%A6%20and%20some%20chopped%20parsley.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Adding%20parsley%20for%20yemista%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d8255a0e5a0018d2ed4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThrow%20in%20half%20of%20your%20chopped%20parsley.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20use%20half%20of%20the%20parsley%20you've%20prepped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThen%2C%20mix%20everything%20together.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mixing%20the%20yemista%20mixture%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d8155a0e5a0018d2ed15%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECook%20your%20ground%20beef%20until%20the%20meat%20has%20browned.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUse%20a%20spatula%20or%20wooden%20spoon%20to%20break%20up%20the%20ground%20beef%2C%20cooking%20it%20until%20the%20meat%20has%20browned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EOnce%20the%20meat%20has%20browned%2C%20add%20the%20rice%20and%20tomato%20%26quot%3Bsauce.%26quot%3B%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Adding%20tomato%20to%20yemista%20mixture%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d8295a0e5a0018d2ed56%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20yemista%20filling%20with%20rice%20and%20tomato%20sauce.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERemember%20you'll%20need%20%E2%85%94%20cup%20of%20rice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMix%20everything%20together%20and%20let%20it%20simmer.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221508%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yemista%20mixture%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d8125a0e5a0018d2ed0d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221759%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYour%20filling%20should%20simmer%20for%20about%20five%20minutes.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20take%20around%20five%20minutes%2C%20until%20most%20of%20the%20water%20in%20the%20sauce%20has%20reduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20don't%20let%20the%20filling%20get%20too%20dry%20%E2%80%94%20we%20need%20some%20liquid%20to%20help%20the%20rice%20cook%20in%20the%20oven.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThrow%20in%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20chopped%20parsley.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yemista%20mixture%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d826adc9990018844b0a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20yemista%20mixture.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGive%20it%20one%20last%20mix%20and%20voil%C3%A0%20%E2%80%94%20your%20filling%20is%20done!%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EUsing%20a%20spoon%2C%20fill%20each%20tomato%20cup%20with%20the%20beef%20and%20rice%20mixture.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Adding%20Yemista%20mixture%20to%20tomatoes%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d81f5a0e5a0018d2ed28%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDon't%20overfill%20the%20tomato%20cups%20with%20the%20filling%20mixture.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMake%20sure%20you%20don't%20overfill%20because%20the%20rice%20will%20expand%20in%20the%20oven.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EYour%20filled%20tomato%20cups%20should%20look%20like%20this.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tomatoes%20with%20Yemista%20mixture%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d8125a0e5a0018d2ed09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20yemista%20tomato%20cups%20with%20the%20filling.%3Cp%3EAnneta%20Konstantinides%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20the%20size%20of%20your%20tomatoes%2C%20you%20might%20have%20some%20extra%20filling.%20Unfortunately%2C%20since%20it%20contains%20raw%20rice%2C%20there's%20not%20much%20you%20can%20do.%20But%20if%20you%20have%20extra%20tomatoes%2C%20you%20can%20always%20scoop%20and%20fill%20them%20with%20the%20extra%20stuffing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlternatively%2C%20just%20adjust%20your%20recipe%20the%20next%20time%20by%20using%20less%20ground%20beef.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThen%2C%20put%20the%20tops%20back%20on%20the%20tomatoes%20and%20add%20some%20water%20and%20olive%20oil.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Adding%20water%20to%20tomatoes%20in%20pan%20for%20yemista%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6318d8065a0e5a0018d2ecfb%3Fformat%3D