-cars-nytimes-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eonly%20cameras%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20that%20will%20help%20the%20company's%20ability%20to%20scale%20a%20robotaxi%20service%20at%20lower%20costs.%20In%20addition%2C%20Tesla%20says%20it%20has%20the%20manufacturing%20capability%20to%20rapidly%20produce%20a%20two-door%2C%20purpose-built%20robotaxi%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-robotaxi-event-cybercab-elon-musk-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECybercab%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20yet%20another%20proposition%20is%20that%20Tesla%20owners%20also%20will%20be%20able%20to%20turn%20their%20cars%20into%20autonomous%20chauffeurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECombined%20with%20an%20AI-powered%20driver%20system%20that%20has%20been%20trained%20on%20%26quot%3Bbillions%20of%20miles%20of%20anonymous%20real-world%20driving%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Tesla%2C%20Musk's%20company%20is%20proposing%20what%20he%20says%20will%20be%20a%20cheaper%20and%20more%20intelligent%20robotaxi%20service%20that%20can%20scale%20faster%20than%20its%20competitors%2C%20like%20Waymo%2C%20at%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20predict%20there%20will%20be%20millions%20of%20Teslas%20operating%20fully%20autonomously%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20next%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20said%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-earnings-call-report-tsla-stock-live-updates-2025-4%23musk-says-the-first-paid-robotaxi-rides-in-austin-will-be-in-the-tesla-model-y%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETesla's%20first-quarter%20earnings%20call%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla's%20success%2C%20however%2C%20rests%20on%20a%20lot%20of%20assumptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlex%20Roy%2C%20general%20partner%20at%20New%20Industry%20VC%20and%20former%20director%20at%20Argo%20AI%2C%20a%20self-driving%20startup%2C%20is%20bullish%20on%20Tesla's%20robotaxi%20vision%20%E2%80%94%20but%20he%20lists%20several%20hurdles%20the%20company%20has%20to%20jump%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%2C%20Tesla%20has%20yet%20to%20show%20evidence%20of%20a%20significant%20operations%20arm%20%E2%80%94%20the%20boring%20but%20crucial%20side%20of%20the%20ride-sharing%20business%20that%20includes%20maintenance%20of%20the%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20significant%20operations%20arm%20to%20maintain%2C%20store%2C%20and%20repair%20the%20vehicles%20and%20that%20is%20very%20close%20or%20inside%20the%20deployment%20geofence%2C%20you%20can't%20be%20in%20the%20robotaxi%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Roy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20area%2C%20he%20said%20Waymo's%20being%20first%20is%20crucial%20and%20makes%20the%20company%20a%20leader%20in%20the%20robotaxi%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20half%20of%20Tesla's%20thesis%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%2C%20Tesla's%20proposal%20to%20turn%20any%20one%20of%20the%20millions%20of%20privately-owned%20cars%20into%20a%20robotaxi%20%E2%80%94%20is%20still%20at%20a%20wait-and-see%20moment%2C%20Roy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20VC%20believes%20that%20Tesla's%20AI%20driver%20will%20only%20be%20as%20good%20as%20what%20Tesla's%20suite%20of%20cameras%20allows%20the%20AI%20driver%20to%20see%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20vast%20amount%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwaymo-cofounder-tesla-robotaxi-data-strategy-self-driving-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereal-world%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20EV%20company%20touts.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERoy%20is%20thinking%20about%20conditions%20where%20visibility%20will%20be%20an%20issue%2C%20such%20as%20foggy%20weather.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaymo%20previously%20demonstrated%20at%20Google%20I%2FO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwaymo-robotaxi-lidar-sensor-versus-cameras-vision-only-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehow%20its%20lidar%20and%20imaging%20radar%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20able%20to%20detect%20humans%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20sandstorm%20or%20a%20pedestrian%20whose%20view%20is%20blocked%20by%20a%20bus%2C%20therefore%20undetectable%20by%20cameras.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoy%20said%20that%20he%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%26quot%3B%20believes%20Tesla%20can%20deploy%20with%20cameras%20only%2C%20but%20with%20limitations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20cannot%20drive%20faster%20or%20better%20than%20the%20limitations%20of%20what%20it%20can%20see%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhereas%2C%20a%20Waymo%20has%20sensors%20with%20additional%20capabilities%20that%20a%20camera%20can't%20see.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPutting%20aside%20the%20limitations%20of%20cameras%2C%20Roy%20said%20Tesla%20will%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20two%20other%20components%20to%20deliver%20a%20robotaxi%20service%20powered%20by%20personally-owned%20vehicles%3A%20a%20good%20user%20experience%20and%2C%20again%2C%20an%20operations%20solution%20for%20managing%20the%20fleet%20of%20personally-owned%20Teslas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20VC%20said%20Tesla%20can%20either%20support%20private%20owners%20with%20cleaning%20and%20maintenance%20through%20its%20own%20operations%2C%20or%20the%20owners%20themselves%20can%20do%20it.%20Turo%2C%20the%20car%20rental%20app%2C%20is%20an%20example%20of%20what%20the%20latter%20solution%20would%20look%20like%2C%20Roy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20Airbnb%20%E2%80%94%20a%20lot%20of%20hosts%20are%20great.%20They're%20not%20all%20great%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BFurthermore%2C%20we%20also%20know%20from%20Turo%20that%20if%20vehicles%20have%20to%20come%20from%20further%20away%2C%20that%20could%20be%20inconvenient.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a7578da3-3293-4999-b89d-c7c330535a11%5C%22%3EThe%20robotaxi%20race%20is%20an%20expensive%20endeavor%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobotaxis-general-motors-cruise-problems-tesla-elon-musk-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECruise%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20once%20a%20formidable%20player%20in%20the%20robotaxi%20space%2C%20burned%20through%20%2410%20billion%20before%20it%20was%20shut%20down%20by%20its%20parent%20company%2C%20General%20Motors%2C%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaymo%2C%20a%20subsidiary%20of%20Alphabet%2C%20announced%20last%20year%20that%20it%20raised%20%245.6%20billion%20from%20outside%20investors.%20In%20addition%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falphabet-is-pouring-billions-into-waymos-self-driving-vehicles-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAlphabet%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20last%20July%20that%20the%20company%20would%20commit%20%245%20billion%20in%20a%20multi-year%20investment%20toward%20its%20robotaxi%20ambitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20consensus%20among%20analysts%20is%20that%20robotaxis%20will%20be%20a%20few-winners-take-most%20outcome%2C%20with%20data%20and%20capital%20being%20key%20to%20survival%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobotaxis-may-mobility-tesla-cybercab-waymo-ford-gm-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebrutal%20business%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20with%20access%20to%20%26quot%3Bdata%20and%20capital%20(to%20fund%20compute)%20remain%20well%20positioned%20to%20drive%20the%20next%20leg%20of%20AV%20deployments%2C%26quot%3B%20Brian%20Nowak%2C%20a%20Morgan%20Stanley%20analyst%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20note%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoy%20and%20some%20AV%20players%20argue%20that%20the%20type%20of%20data%20self-driving%20companies%20have%20access%20to%20may%20be%20more%20important%20than%20the%20quantity%20of%20data%20they%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmnon%20Shashua%2C%20CEO%20of%20Mobileye%2C%20said%20at%20a%20Los%20Angeles%20conference%20in%20April%20that%20the%20amount%20of%20real-world%20data%20available%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bexhausted%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20why%20simulated%20data%20has%20been%20helpful%20for%20exploring%20rare%20driving%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20have%20said%2C%20'Oh%20data%20is%20th